  "title": "What OMS‑on‑PSS Actually Means",
  "slug": "what-omsonpss-actually-means",
  "content": "\n          <h2><style class=\"WebKit-mso-list-quirks-style\">\n<!--\n/* Style Definitions */\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\n\t{mso-style-unhide:no;\n\tmso-style-qformat:yes;\n\tmso-style-parent:\"\";\n\tmargin:0cm;\n\tmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\n\tfont-size:12.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Muli;\n\tmso-fareast-font-family:Aptos;\n\tmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman \\(Body CS\\)\";\n\tmso-font-kerning:1.0pt;\n\tmso-ligatures:standardcontextual;\n\tmso-fareast-language:EN-US;}\n.MsoChpDefault\n\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\n\tmso-default-props:yes;\n\tfont-family:Muli;\n\tmso-ascii-font-family:Muli;\n\tmso-fareast-font-family:Aptos;\n\tmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;\n\tmso-hansi-font-family:Muli;\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman \\(Body CS\\)\";\n\tmso-fareast-language:EN-US;}\n@page WordSection1\n\t{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\n\tmargin:72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt;\n\tmso-header-margin:36.0pt;\n\tmso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\n\tmso-paper-source:0;}\ndiv.WordSection1\n\t{page:WordSection1;}\n /* List Definitions */\n @list l0\n\t{mso-list-id:885340290;\n\tmso-list-template-ids:392571422;}\n@list l0:level1\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:36.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Symbol;}\n@list l0:level2\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:o;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:72.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:\"Courier New\";\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\n@list l0:level3\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:108.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level4\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:144.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level5\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:180.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level6\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:216.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level7\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:252.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level8\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:288.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level9\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:324.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n\n-->\n</style><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">Running an&nbsp;Order Management System (OMS) on top of an existing Passenger Service System (PSS)&nbsp;delivers strong commercial upside with far lower risk and cost than a full move to an&nbsp;OOSD‑style “new‑generation” PSS. For most airlines, this layered approach is a pragmatic path to modern retailing, not a compromise.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">What OMS‑on‑PSS actually means<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">An OMS‑on‑PSS architecture keeps the legacy PSS as the&nbsp;operational backbone&nbsp;(inventory, reservations, PNRs, interline, DCS) while adding an OMS layer that handles&nbsp;offers, orders, payments, and servicing&nbsp;across channels.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">The PSS still “owns” flights and segments; the OMS owns the&nbsp;customer‑facing order, enabling NDC‑style shopping, dynamic bundles, and post‑booking changes without rewriting core operations.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">Key business benefits of OMS‑on‑PSS<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">1. Faster time‑to‑market for modern retailing<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">An OMS‑on‑PSS lets airlines launch&nbsp;NDC‑ready offers, rich bundles, and partner content&nbsp;in months rather than years, because you are not waiting for a full PSS replacement.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">New products, services and ancillary packages can be configured in the OMS and tested in specific channels while the rest of the business keeps running on the existing PSS.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">2. Lower risk and lower cost<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">Migrating to an OOSD‑style PSS typically requires a&nbsp;multi‑year, multi‑vendor transformation&nbsp;touching inventory, pricing, accounting, interline, and GDS connectivity.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">In contrast, an OMS‑on‑PSS is&nbsp;incremental: you add order management for direct channels first, then extend to NDC and GDS, reusing the PSS where it still works well.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">3. Better control over commercial logic and data<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">With an OMS on top, airlines can&nbsp;decouple commercial rules&nbsp;(pricing, bundling, promos, loyalty) from the PSS, which remains focused on operations.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">Orders “live forever” in the OMS, enabling rich&nbsp;CRM, personalization, and lifecycle marketing&nbsp;that legacy PNR‑centric systems struggle to support.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">4. Easier experimentation and innovation<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">An OMS‑on‑PSS acts as a&nbsp;retail orchestrator: you can plug in new suppliers, payment gateways, and partner products without touching the PSS core.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">This makes it simpler to run&nbsp;A/B tests, new concepts, or ancillary strategies&nbsp;in selected markets or channels, then scale what works.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">5. Smoother transition toward OOSD<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">An OMS‑on‑PSS effectively&nbsp;builds the “order layer”&nbsp;that OOSD architectures later assume as native.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">When the airline is ready to replace the PSS, much of the order‑centric logic, data model, and channel integrations already exist, reducing the complexity of the final migration.</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">Why OOSD‑only is often overkill<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">OOSD aim to&nbsp;replace the PSS entirely&nbsp;with an order‑centric platform covering offer, order, settlement, and delivery.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">For many airlines, this is&nbsp;too big of a leap&nbsp;unless there is a strategic decision to “rip and replace”, otherwise it risks budget overruns, operational disruption, and long stabilization periods.</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin: 0cm; font-size: medium; font-family: Muli; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; color: black;\">When OMS‑on‑PSS makes the most sense<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-style: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-line: none; text-decoration-thickness: auto; text-decoration-style: solid;\"><li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\n     auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">The airline wants&nbsp;NDC, dynamic bundling, and richer ancillaries&nbsp;but cannot afford or justify a full PSS replacement.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\n     auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">The current PSS is&nbsp;operationally stable but commercially limiting, and the business wants to test modern retailing in direct and NDC channels first.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color:black;mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\n     auto;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list 36.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Leadership wants&nbsp;quick wins&nbsp;(revenue uplift, better CX, improved data) while preserving option to move to OOSD later.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li></ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"font-size: medium; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\"><style class=\"WebKit-mso-list-quirks-style\">\n<!--\n/* Style Definitions */\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\n\t{mso-style-unhide:no;\n\tmso-style-qformat:yes;\n\tmso-style-parent:\"\";\n\tmargin:0cm;\n\tmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\n\tfont-size:12.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Muli;\n\tmso-fareast-font-family:Aptos;\n\tmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman \\(Body CS\\)\";\n\tmso-font-kerning:1.0pt;\n\tmso-ligatures:standardcontextual;\n\tmso-fareast-language:EN-US;}\n.MsoChpDefault\n\t{mso-style-type:export-only;\n\tmso-default-props:yes;\n\tfont-family:Muli;\n\tmso-ascii-font-family:Muli;\n\tmso-fareast-font-family:Aptos;\n\tmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;\n\tmso-hansi-font-family:Muli;\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman \\(Body CS\\)\";\n\tmso-fareast-language:EN-US;}\n@page WordSection1\n\t{size:612.0pt 792.0pt;\n\tmargin:72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt 72.0pt;\n\tmso-header-margin:36.0pt;\n\tmso-footer-margin:36.0pt;\n\tmso-paper-source:0;}\ndiv.WordSection1\n\t{page:WordSection1;}\n /* List Definitions */\n @list l0\n\t{mso-list-id:885340290;\n\tmso-list-template-ids:392571422;}\n@list l0:level1\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:36.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Symbol;}\n@list l0:level2\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:o;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:72.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:\"Courier New\";\n\tmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\n@list l0:level3\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:108.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level4\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:144.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level5\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:180.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level6\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:216.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level7\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:252.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level8\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:288.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n@list l0:level9\n\t{mso-level-number-format:bullet;\n\tmso-level-text:;\n\tmso-level-tab-stop:324.0pt;\n\tmso-level-number-position:left;\n\ttext-indent:-18.0pt;\n\tmso-ansi-font-size:10.0pt;\n\tfont-family:Wingdings;}\n\n-->\n</style></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"font-size: medium; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"font-size: medium; caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0); color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">In short, an OMS on top of a PSS is a&nbsp;low‑risk, high‑leverage stepping stone&nbsp;to airline retailing: it unlocks order‑based commerce, data‑driven marketing, and channel agility without forcing a premature, capital‑intensive OOSD overhaul.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p></h2>\n        ",
